      "id": 1,
      "options": {
        "content": "## AI Energy Optimisation\n\nThe original D3.3 direction targeted water-based heat reuse and water regime optimisation. In the absence of a suitable liquid-cooled testbed, the work was redirected toward **AI-based telemetry modelling** for predictive energy management.\n\nThis view shows how telemetry-driven models can support **energy-aware workload orchestration** and **predictive energy management** using currently available server signals.",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "pluginVersion": "11.0.0",
      "title": "AI Energy Optimisation",
      "transparent": false,
      "type": "text"
    },
    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "postgres",
        "uid": "postgres-ops"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 7,
        "w": 5,
        "x": 4,
        "y": 4
      },
      "id": 2,
      "options": {
        "content": "### LSTM\nTelemetry-driven benchmark\n\n- **Type:** time-series neural network\n- **Purpose:** Temporal prediction of server load and power\n- **Accuracy:** 96.90%\n- **Energy:** 6223 J\n- **Interpretation:** Highest sequential modelling complexity but materially higher energy demand than tree-based alternatives.",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "pluginVersion": "11.0.0",
      "title": "LSTM",
      "transparent": false,
      "type": "text"
    },
    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "postgres",
        "uid": "postgres-ops"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 7,
        "w": 5,
        "x": 9,
        "y": 4
      },
      "id": 3,
      "options": {
        "content": "### Random Forest\nTelemetry-driven benchmark\n\n- **Type:** ensemble learning\n- **Purpose:** Nonlinear energy-temperature relationship modelling\n- **Accuracy:** 97.45%\n- **Energy:** 2103 J\n- **Interpretation:** Stable nonlinear baseline with moderate energy cost and solid predictive behaviour.",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "pluginVersion": "11.0.0",
      "title": "Random Forest",
      "transparent": false,
      "type": "text"
    },
    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "postgres",
        "uid": "postgres-ops"
      },
      "gridPos": {
        "h": 7,
        "w": 5,
        "x": 14,
        "y": 4
      },
      "id": 4,
      "options": {
        "content": "### XGBoost\n**Preferred family**\n\n- **Type:** gradient boosting\n- **Purpose:** High-accuracy power and energy forecasting\n- **Accuracy:** 97.83%\n- **Energy:** 1245 J\n- **Interpretation:** Strong balance of predictive quality and low energy demand, making it highly suitable for orchestration loops.",
        "mode": "markdown"
      },
      "pluginVersion": "11.0.0",
      "title": "XGBoost",
      "transparent": false,
      "type": "text"
    },
    {
      "datasource": {
        "type": "postgres",
